<br>
After we were &quot;brothers&quot;, we distanced ourselves from everyone else.  We used to talk on the phone every night for 3 hours, about anything and everything.  I would drop everything for him and he the saem for me.  I can honestly say that he was the only person I've ever fallen in love with.  True love (yes I believe in it...), not just a crush or something like that.<br>
<br>
Basically after that year, he put a barrier between himself and the world, and I never thought I'd see him again.  This was three years ago.  Tonight I saw him for the first time since then randomly at a bar.  As soon as he walked in the room a huge smile came to my face because I just couldn't believe it.<br>
<br>
He saw me and waved from across the room, so I went over to talk to him.  After a few minutes I offered to give him my number so we could keep in touch, but he said,<br>
&quot;You're a nice guy, but I really don't want to get involved with a lot of people.&quot;<br>
<br>
I think he noticed my abrupt change in temperment, because then he said &quot;you're not bothering me&quot; but I really didn't have the heart to say anything else to him after that.  <br>
<br>
I've waited what felt like a lifetime for that moment.  I've even dreamed of its occurrence.  It would have been easier to have heard that he had died (however awful that would have been), than to have to face a shadow of his former self.<br>
<br>
I understand people change for whatever reason, but I don't understand how someone with good conscience can completely disregard someone who they were once so close to.  I never felt more alone...<br>
<br>
((I'll put myself last, so he might be first, for I know no other type of love...))<br>
-Gio <p><img border=0 src="http://pic7.picturetrail.com/VOL217/1032248/1929737/25460459.jpg" />

